<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-14T17:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-14T17:36:00-05:00" n="841" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.516/116</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-14T16:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 14, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>228. Department’s 198, December 28, 6 p.m. Minister of Finance has just
                            replied that in order to give the proper answer to the suggestions
                            contained in said telegram it will be necessary for the Department to
                            refer to concrete cases of proposed drastic measures <pb facs="0709" n="633" xml:id="pg_633"/> as so far the Government has only issued a
                            decree by which banks of issue are required to comply with provisions of
                            banking laws which were in existence when the revolution began.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>